ind":"italic_en","text":"Unpreparedly, suddenly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unexpectedly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyhFA","text_ar":"بَدِيهًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"by Golius, as on the authority of J, but I do not find it in the S in the present article.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA=hu badiyhapF","text_ar":"رَا=هُ بَدِيهَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He saw him suddenly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unexpectedly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyhapu Alr~aA^oYi","text_ar":"بَدِيهَةُ الرَّاْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Suddenly formed, unpremeditated, judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyhapN","text_ar":"بَدِيهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budaAhapN","text_ar":"بُدَاهَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming, of speech, without premeditation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming suddenly, unexpectedly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unawares."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) ―         -b3-  And ↓ the latter, [and more commonly the former,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An intuitive knowledge, notion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"idea; such as that one is the half of two;"},{"kind":"text","text":"being,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to knowledge, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyEN","text_ar":"بَدِيعٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull:) [or] the former signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculty of judging rightly at the first of an unexpected occurrence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intuition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intuitive perception:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] accord. to ' Alee-Ibn-Dháfir El-Haddád, it signifies primarily"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotijaAlN fiY AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"اِرْتِجَالٌ فِى الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faculty of extemporizing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speaking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"composing, extemporaneously, impromptu, without premeditation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and predominantly, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poetizing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"versifying, impromptu, without premeditation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consideration: except that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtjAl","text_ar":"ارتجال"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is quicker than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bdyhp","text_ar":"بديهة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw badiyhapK","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو بَدِيهَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a faculty of judging rightly at the first of an unexpected occurrence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN *uw","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyhapK HasanapK","text_ar":"بَدِيهَةٍ حَسَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has a good faculty of extemporizing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of uttering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating, things by means of the promptness of his intelligence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bdA^","text_ar":"بدا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyoapN","text_ar":"بَدِيَْةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA maEoluwmN","text_ar":"هٰذَا مَعْلُومٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY badaAy^ihi AlEuquwli","text_ar":"فِى بَدَايِهِ العُقُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is known among the intuitive notions of intellects;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intuitively"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, * TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAy^ihu","text_ar":"بَدَايِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyhapN","text_ar":"بَدِيهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the phrase, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu badaAy^ihu","text_ar":"لَهُ بَدَايِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAy^iEu","text_ar":"بَدَايِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has new"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admirable, things that he utters"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,) in speech, or language, and poetry, and in answering, or replying: but here it is not improbable that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be a substitute for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Kull"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}